      <article data-history-node-id="37" about="/article/open-letter.html" typeof="schema:Article">

  
      <span property="schema:name" content="Open Letter" class="hidden"></span>


  
  <div>
      <div class="layout layout--onecol">
    <div  class="layout__region layout__region--content">
      <div class="views-element-container">
  
    
      <div><div class="js-view-dom-id-6fdae6bba2beb277b2009032c6deeef3de20309e48eacdf07773db04045778a7">
  
  
  

  
  
  

      <div class="views-row"><div class="views-field views-field-type"><span class="field-content"><strong>Organic Media</strong></span></div><div class="views-field views-field-body"><div class="field-content"><p>Hi,</p>

<p>I hope you're doing well. Thank you for your encouraging words and interest in our initiative at ReLeaf. </p>

<p>Here's some more details on the businesses we're initially partnering with and the type of waste we're dealing with:</p>

<p>1. Automotive Repair Shops: They provide us with assorted car parts like bumpers, fenders, and doors. We aim to repurpose these materials in innovative ways.</p>

<p>2. Austin School of Furniture and other Wood Manufacturers: We obtain sawdust from them, useful as soil and compost enrichment.</p>

<p>3. Businesses with Palettes: Wood pallets serve as excellent foundations for our living walls.</p>

<p>4. Breweries and Distilleries: They have carbon cellulose filter pads (16"x16") which can be transformed for various purposes such as water filtering. They also have organic waste mash, valuable in compost.</p>

<p>6. Plant Companies, Nurseries, Landscape Suppliers: They provide us with Polypropylene #5 plastic pots and trays which can be utilized as planters or pockets for planters.</p>

<p>Our business model remains adaptable, and as we grow, we anticipate welcoming more business types and cooperative member-owners into our network.</p>

<p>Looking forward to further discussion and your invaluable input!</p>

<p>Best regards,</p>

<p>Bryce</p></div></div><div class="views-field views-field-field-w-a-s-t-e-words"><span class="views-label views-label-field-w-a-s-t-e-words">W.A.S.T.E.: Words Assisting Sustainable Transformation &amp; Ecology </span><div class="field-content"><ul><li><a href="/releaf.html" hreflang="en">ReLeaf</a>
